Bumper to finish off the over. Ducked comfortably by Ngidi.
Good length ball on middle, Sipamla tries to defend but it hits him on the splice of the bat.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Shortish and on off, straightening a bit, Sipamla gets squared up and pushes it out to point. Looks for a run but is sent back.
A bouncer now, ducked under by Lutho.
A length ball around middle and off from 'round the wicket, Sipamla does well to block it to the off side.
Effort delivery. Chameera digs in a short ball around off, it zips off the surface and Sipamla sways away from the line.
Shortish around off, angling across, Ngidi sways away from this one and lets it go.
Fuller this time on middle, Ngidi drives it towards mid off and collects a quick single.
Length ball around middle and off, Sipamla gets behind the line and blocks this out.

OUT! CAUGHT! 5 wickets for Vishva Fernando. He has bowled extremely well and thoroughly deserves this 5-fer. A shortish ball around off, Sipamla looks to punch it from the back foot but ends up edging it towards the fielder at gully. Shanaka there jumps and takes a good catch. South Africa are bowled out for 302 and have a lead of 145 runs.
Ngidi starts off with a back of length ball on middle, Dimuth looks to flicks but gets hit on the pads and the ball lobs towards the slip cordon.
A back of a length on middle, Dimuth looks to defend but gets an inside edgeÂ on his pads. A nervy start for the skipper.
Shortish around off, Dimuth hops and keeps this one out.
Length around middle, Karunaratne defends it towards mid-wicket.
Back of a length around off, Karunaratne looks to play on the off side, but the ball hits the inside part of the bat and lobs towards mid-wicket.
Length ball outside off, Dimuth lets it go through to the keeper. Maiden to start from Ngidi.
A good length ball on middle and off, Perera defends it back from the middle of the bat.
Extra bounce hurries the batsman! On a good length around leg, Perera tries to work it on the leg side but the ballÂ jumps and strikes him on the gloves. That would have hurt.
Nortje serves a back of a length ball on off, hitting the deck hard as usual, Kusal covers the line and blocks it safely.
A length ball on leg,Â Perera works it off his pads but finds mid-wicket.
A single on this occasion. The line from Nortje is straight again and Perera tucks it away towards square leg for a run.
Angling away from the batsman, on a length, Karunaratne taps it down towards point and Perera looks for a run. He is sent back as Bavuma attacks the ball.
Play and a miss! Length ball outside off, Perera looks to smash that but ends up missing it altogether.

OUT! BOWLED! Ngidi strikes early and Perera can't repeat his 1st innings heroics. A length ball around off, nips back in sharply and goes between the bat and pad of Perera to hit the top of middle and leg. South Africa strike early and it's a massive blow for Sri Lanka. Lahiru Thirimanne has joined his skipper in the middle.
Length ball just outside off, comes back in after pitching. Thirimanne lets it go to the keeper.
Length outside off, Thirimanne is not interested in playing that.
Length outside off, Thirimanne again covers his stumps and lets it go.
Length around middle and off, Thirimanne looks to defend but ends up getting an inside edge onto his pads.
Good length ball on middle, Karunaratne gets off the mark by flicking this to deep square leg for a single.
Good pace from Nortje! Good length ball outside off, Thirimanne looks to defend but the ball whizzes past the outside edge and it goes to the keeper.
Good length ball down the leg side, Thirimanne looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball on the pads, Thirimanne looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.

Up in the air but does not carry! This is excellent bowling from Nortje! Short ball on middle, Thirimanne looks to defend but the ball gets big on him. It takes the top edge and lobs towards point. The fielder comes charging in but it falls short.
Length ball outside off, Thirimanne shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball outside off, Karunaratne lets it through to the keeper.
On a length outside off, Karunaratne watches it carefully and then shoulders arms to it.

EDGED AND FOUR! Luck favouring Karunaratne! Good length ball outside off, little bit of shape away. Karunaratne looks to drive but it takes the outside edge and goes between third slip and gully for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.

Aerial but safe! Fullish ball outside off, Karunaratne drives it uppishly towards the point fielder. It bounces short of the fielder and then goes past Maharaj. He chases it down and then pulls it back in. Two taken.
Good length ball outside off, Dimuth pushes it to point.
Good length ball outside off, Lahiru lets it go to the keeper.
Full ball outside off, Thirimanne pushes it to cover.
On a length on off, Thirimanne plays it to the off side. He wants the single but is sent back.
Fullish ball outside off, Thirimanne shoulders arms to it.
Full ball on off, Lahiru plays it to cover for a dot.
Good length ball on middle, Thirimanne defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Flicked uppishly but safe! Full ball on middle, angling in. Karunaratne flicks i uppsihly but wide of the fielder at mid-wicket. It races away to the fence.
PLAY AND A MISS! Short ball outside off, Dimuth looks to cut but misses it altogether.
Full ball outside off, Dimuth shoulders arms to it.
On a length outside off, Karunaratne lets it go to the keeper.
Ngidi goes full and outside off, Karunaratne makes another leave to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball on off, LahiruÂ defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length ball on off, Thirimanne goes on his back foot and looks to defend but it takes the bottom edge and almost rolls onto the stumps. Luckily for Thirimanne, it does not.
Almost chopped on! Good length ball outside off, Thirimanne looks to punch it off the back foot but it takes the inside edge and rolls past the leg stump.
FOUR! Fantastic drive from Thirimanne! Full ball outside off, Thirimanne lunges forward and creams the drive through the covers for a boundary.
On a length outside off, left alone by Lahiru.
Good length ball outside off, Thirimanne shoulders arms to it.
Full ball on middle, Karunaratne defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length ball on off, Karunaratne defends it towards the cover region.
Good length ball on middle, worked to square leg.
Fullish ball on middle, Karunaratne flicks it to square leg for a dot.
Very full outside off, Dimuth lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball on middle, Karunaratne defends it back to the bowler. TEA ON DAY 2.
Good length ball outside off, Thirimanne shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball outside off, Thirimanne lets it go to the keeper.
Comes around the wicket and bowls a full ball outside off, Thirimanne makes a leave to this one.
Short ball around off, Thirimanne sways away from it.
Full ball outside off, Thirimanne has no problems in leaving it alone.
FOUR! That's nicely played from Thirimanne! Good length ball outside off, Thirimanne drives it through the cover-point region for a boundary.
Length ball around off, Dimuth blocks this out on the on side.
Length ball around middle and leg, Dimuth plays it down towards square leg.
A bit fuller this time on middle, Karunaratne covers his stumps and blocks it out.
Short and wide outside off, Dimuth pushes it in the gap at cover point. They take a couple before Markram chases it down and returns it back.
FOUR! Beautiful timing. AÂ length ball on middle, KarunaratneÂ stands tall and just times this one through the gap at mid-wicket and collects a boundary.
Good length ball in the channel outside off, angling across, Dimuth lets it go.
Good length ball outside off, Thirimanne shoulders arms to it.
PLAY AND A MISS! Poor shot from Thirimanne! Good length ball outside off, ThirimanneÂ looks to cut but fails to get any bat on it.
FOUR! Beautifully driven by Lahiru! Good length ball outside off, Thirimanne strides forward and creams the drive through the cover region for a boundary.
Full ball on off, Thirimanne defends it to the cover region.
Short ball around middle, Lahiru ducks under it.
Shortish around middle, Lahiru sits under it.
Fuller length around off, Dimuth covers the line and defends this out.
Length ball angling across the left-hander, Karunaratne lets it go through to the keeper.
NO BALL! Fuller around off, Dimuth looks to drive but the ball hits the inner part of the bat and lobs towards mid-wicket. Mulder has overstepped on this one.
Fuller length in the channel outside off, Dimuth lets it go.
Fuller around off, KarunaratneÂ pushes this one towards the right of the cover fielder and calls his partner for a quick run.
Length ball outside off, Thirimanne leaves it alone.
Short of a length around off, Lahiru stands tall and bunts this out.
Full ball on middle, Karunaratne looks to flick but it takes the inner half of the bat and rolls to the deep mid-wicket region for a single.
Good length ball on off, Thirimanne drives it towards mid on where the fielder makes a half stop, allowing the batters to take a single.
Short ball around middle, Dimuth ducks under it.
Full ball on middle, Karunaratne pushes it back to the bowler.
FOUR! That's really well played! Nortje bangs it in short on off, Karunaratne rocks on his back foot and then pulls it to deep mid-wicket region for a boundary.
FOUR! Beautifully played from the Sri Lankan skipper. Full ball on middle, Karunaratne flicks it through the mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Fullish ball outside off inviting the drive, Lahiru refuses his invitation and lets it go.
Fuller ball on leg, ThirimanneÂ looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. Huge appeal from the bowler but the umpire is unmoved.
Length ball but too wide outside off, Lahiru has no intentions in playing that.
A good length ball outside off, but not close enough to force Thirimanne to play at it.

FOUR! Lovely drive. An overpitched ball on middle and leg, ThirimanneÂ prods forward and drives this past the bowler towards the mid on boundary. It was in the air for a while but a tough chance for Mulder in his followthrough.
Fullish length outside off, Lahiru lets it go through to the keeper.
Full ball on middle, Karunaratne defends it out onto the pitch.
Short ball outside off, Dimuth looks to pull but misses.
BEATEN! Almost found the edge! Briliant delivery! Good length ball outside off, Karunaratne prods forward to defend but gets beaten.

FOUR! That was half a chance! Sipamla has his hands on his face! Good length ball around off, Karunaratne punches it back. Sipamla picked it up late and it goes past him and into the fence for a boundary.
On middle, Dimuth works it to mid-wicket.
Full ball outside off, driven to deep cover for a single. 50-run stand comes up.
Fuller length in the channel outside off, Dimuth shoulders arms to this one.
Comes closer to the stumps this time does Mulder, but Dimuth is solid in his defense.
Length ball around off, Karunaratne plays it with soft hands towards point and attempts to take a run, but gets back as his partner says "No".
FOUR! Superb timing on that one. Fuller ball around middle and leg, Karunaratne flicks it nicely towards the fine leg fence and moves to 36.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
Length ball around middle, Karunaratne flicks it towards deep square and takes a run to keep the strike. Mulder gets a warning for running on the pitch.
Full ball on middle, DK pushes it to mid on.
Fullish ball on off, Karunaratne defends it to cover and wants a single but Thirimanne is not interested and sends his skipper back.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
Back of a length ball on middle, Dimuth hops and then works it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on off, Karunaratne punches it back to the bowler.
Full ball outside off, pushed to mid off.
Mulder comes round the wicket after being warned in his previous over. Starts off with a length ball outside off, Thirimanne lets it go.
Length ball angling into Thirimanne, he tucks this towards deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length around off, Karunaratne pushes this on the off side and attempts to take a run, but decides against it.
Length ball around off, driven down towards mid off.
Length ball outside off, Dimuth looks to play on the off side, but the ball hits the inner part and goes towards mid-wicket.
Fullish ball outside off, Karunaratne drives it straight but Mulder stops that in his followthrough.
Good length ball on off, Thirimanne taps it to the off side for a single.
On a length outside off, Karunaratne punches it to cover-point and takes off for a single. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses.
FOUR! Cracking drive from Thirimanne! Fullish ball outside off, Thirimanne fully commits to the shot and drives it through the covers for a boundary.
BEATEN! Good comeback from Sipamla! Good length ball outside off, it nips away. Thirimanne looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
BEATEN! Another good nut from Sipamla! Back of a length ball around off, Thirimanne looks to block but fails to make any connection.
Brilliant! Top stuff from Lutho! Back of a length ball outside off, LahiruÂ looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
FOUR! EDGY! A wide ball outside off, Karunaratne looks to play the cut shot but gets an outside edge which flies overÂ the fielder at gully towards the third man fence.

OUCH! That would have hurt. A length ball around off, straightens after pitching. Dimuth looks to defend but the ball bounces extra and hits him flush on his left thumb. His left hand comes off from the bat and the ball lobs on the off side.
Fuller ball on middle and leg, Karunaratne flicks this one aerially to the right of the fielder at fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Driven firmly. A fullish ball outside off, Thirimanne crouches low and creams this one towards the cover point boundary. Good batting this by Lahiru.

FOUR! Back to back boundaries for Thirimanne. A fuller ball this time on middle, Lahiru flicks this one elegantly towards the mid-wicket boundary. He is really looking good and compact at the crease is Thirimanne.
Length ball outside off, Thirimanne defends it with soft hands towards the right of the fielder at gully. Good over this for Sri Lanka as 13 runs came of it.
Full ball on middle, Karunaratne works it to mid-wicket.
Short ball around off, Karunaratne looks to pull at first but then decides to sway away from it.
Full ball on middle, Dimuth plays it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Nicely played! Full ball on middle, Karunaratne drives it through mid on and picks up another boundary.
FOUR! And again! These two are looking good! Fifty for Dimuth Karunaratne! 25th in Test cricket! Fullish ball on middle, Karunaratne plays it wide of mid on for a boundary.
On a length on middle, Dimuth works it to the leg side for a single.
Short and wide outside off, Karunaratne throws his bat at that and hits it towards the fielder at deep point for a single.
Length ball outside off, Thirimanne lets it go.
A close leaveÂ by Thirimanne. A length ball outside off, comes back after pitching and misses the off pole by a little margin.
Short of a length around off, Lahiru stands tall and defends this down the ground.
Length ball around off, Thirimanne prods forward and plays it straight to covers.

OUT! CAUGHT! A nothing delivery brings about Thirimanne's downfall. A length ball down the leg side, Thirimanne looks to tuckÂ it behind but ends up glovingÂ it straight to de Kock who accepts the catch gleefully. A good little partnership comes to an end. Just what South Africa needed. Sri Lanka trail by 59.
FOUR! Good length ball outside off, Karunaratne looks to drive but it takes the outside edge and goes through the gully region for a boundary.
Full ball on middle, DK works it to mid on.
Back of a length ball on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Good length ball outside off, Dimuth punches it to cover.
Well fielded! Full ball on middle, Karunaratne flicks it through mid-wicket and picks up a couple before the fielder cuts it off.
Short ball around middle, Karunaratne looks to pull but misses andÂ it goes over the stumps towards the keeper.

OUT! CAUGHT! Two similar wickets for Ngidi here. A nothing ball sliding down the leg, Mendis looks to tuck it behind but finds a flying de Kock behind, who stretchesÂ to his left and takes the catch with a reverse cup. Brilliant catchÂ by the South AfricanÂ captain. Kusal Mendis is gone for a golden duck. Sri Lanka lose their 3rd. Mendis was out for a duck in the first innings as well. End of a poor series for him.
A length ball outside off, Minod is not interested in playing that as he declines Ngidi his hat-trick.
Short of a length on middle, Minod hops and defends this one on the on side.
Fuller ball outside off, Bhanuka leaves it alone.
Fuller ball around off, Bhanuka drives this one to the left of covers, but Bavuma there dives and stops the ball. Good fieldingÂ by Bavuma.
Length ball in the channel outside off, Bhanuka lets it go. A wicket maiden by Lungi Ngidi.
Good length ball on middle, Karunaratne works it to mid off.
Full ball on middle, Karunaratne looks to drive but it goes off the inner half of the bat towards the bowler.
Short ball on middle, Dimuth pulls it wide of deep square leg for a couple.
Very full ball outside off, Karunaratne digs it out towards cover.
MISFIELD AND FOUR! Poor stuff from Elgar! Back of a length ball outside off, Karunaratne punches it towards cover. Elgar fails to collect and the ball goes for a boundary.
Full ball on middle, keeping a little low. Karunaratne gets his bat down in time and works it to deep square leg for a single.
A length ball in the channel outside off, Karunaratne shoulders arms to it.
Short of a length but way outside off, Dimuth is not interested in playing at that.
Fullish ball outside off, Karunaratne drives this straight to mid off.
FOUR! Nicely played. A fullish ball on middle, Karunaratne leans on the drive and places it perfectly down the ground towards the mid on fence.

FOUR! Back to back boundaries for Karunaratne. An overpitched ball around off, Dimuth drives it aerially past Ngidi, who fails to get a hand to it. The ball runs away towards the fence at long on. Karunratne is batting beautifully here.
Good comeback by Ngidi. A length ball seamsÂ away viciously after pitching. Dimuth lets it go.
Short ball on middle, Bhanuka looks to fend it away but it takes the gloves and goes towards the off side for a single.
Short ball on the pads, Karunaratne looks to tuckÂ but it takes the pads and goes to square leg for a leg bye.

OUT! CAUGHT! What a wonderful catch from Keshav Maharaj! He might not be bowling but has contributed well in the field now. Brilliant catch from the spinner! Short ball around off, Bhanuka looks to pull but it takes the top edge and goes towards mid-wicket. Keshav Maharaj runs backwards, keeps his eyes on the ball and then dives full lengthÂ to take a brilliant catch. Sri Lanka trail by 36 runs.
FOUR BYES! Short ball around middle, Karunaratne ducks under it. Quinton de Kock hops but fails to collect as the ball races to the fence behind.
Back of a length ball on middle, Dimuth works it to mid-wicket.
Short ball outside off, keeping a little low after pitching.Â Karunaratne looks to pull but fails to make any connection.
Beaten! Top nut this from Ngidi. A length ball outside off, jags away after pitching, missing the outside edge of Dickwella by just a whisker.
Fuller length outside off, Dickwella lets it go through to the keeper.
Dickwella is off the mark as he pushes this fuller ball outside off towards deep point for a single.

Close! AÂ fuller length around middle and off, Karunaratne looks to defend but gets an outside edge towards du Plessis at second slip. He misfields and allows a single. Karunaratne played that with soft hands.
Another edge. A good length around off, Dickella looks to defendÂ but gets an outside edge which falls just short of du Plessis again at second slip.
Length ball in the channel outside off, left alone by Dickwella.
FOUR! Well played! Good length ball outside off, Karunaratne guides it through the gully region for a boundary.
Back of a length ball on middle, Dimuth tucks it to the deep square leg region for a single.
FOUR! Runs flowing in this over! Good length ball outside off, Dickwella guides it past the gully fielder and into the third man fence.
Short ball around off, Dickwella looks to play the upper cut but misses. Wided.
Back of a length ball outside off, Niroshan punches it through cover for a single.
Good length ball on middle, Dimuth nudges it to mid-wicket for a single.
Quick run! Good length ball on middle, Dickwella works it down to mid on and picks up a quick single.
BEATEN! Beautiful ballÂ by Ngidi. A fuller length ball around off, shapes away after pitching and misses the edge of Dickwella's bat by not much.
Length ball in the channel outside off, Dickwella leaves it alone.
Fuller ball on middle, Dickwella gets behind the line and defends it towards mid off.
Back of a length on middle, Dickwella pushes this one towards cover for no run.

FOUR! EDGY! A fuller ball around off inviting the drive. Dickwella accepts the invitation and goes for the drive but gets an outside edge which flies through the gap between third slip and gully. Great bowlingÂ by Ngidi. Unlucky not to get his man here.
Back of a length around off, Dickwella pushes it through the covers and takes a quick run to keep strike.
BEATEN! What a ball from Nortje! Short ball around off, it zips away after pitching. Dickwella looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full ball on off, Dickwella looks to drive but it takes the outside edge and goes towards gully where the fielder does well to stop it.
Full ball on middle, Dickwella flicks it to the mid-wicket region for a single. 2000 Test runs for Dickwella.
Length ball on middle, Karunaratne works it to mid-wicket.
Full ball on middle, Dimuth tucks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Short ball around middle, Dickwella looks to play the upper cut but misses.
Fuller ball outside off, Karunaratne pushes this one towards deep point and takes a run.
BEATEN! A length ball around off, keeps low after pitching and misses the edge of Dickwella's bat.
Shortish around off, Dickwella stands tall and bunts this on the on side.
Close! A fuller length outside off, Dickwella looks to drive away from his body, gets an inside edge which misses the stumps and runs towards fine leg. A single taken.
BEATEN! A length ball around off, shapes away after pitching, Dickella looks to defendÂ that one but gets beaten.
Short of a length outside off, Dickwella this time lets it go through to the keeper.
Full ball outside off, Dickwella shoulders arms to it.
PLAY AND A MISS! Nicely bowled! Full ball outside off, Dickwella looks to drive but the ball whizzes past the outside edge and goes to de Kock.
Low full toss outside off, Dickwella looks to drive but it takes the inside edge and goes to the off side.
Back of a length ball on off, Dickwella stands tall and then defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length ball on off, Niroshan pushes it to cover for a single.
On a length on middle, Karunaratne works it to the leg side.
BEATEN! A length ball outside off, shapes away after pitching. Dickwella hangs his bat out but is lucky that theÂ ball missed the outside edge.
BetterÂ from Niroshan. A length ball outside off, NDÂ leaves it alone this time.
Length ball around off, jags back to hit Dickwella high on his pads, as he already hadÂ made up his mind to leave.
Length ball around off, Dickwella pushes it towards cover.
PLAY AND A MISS! Good length ballÂ inviting Dickwella to drive, he goes through the shot but the ball whizzes past his outside edge.
Length ball around off, comes back in, Dickwella watchfully leaves that alone. Good testing over this by Mulder.
On a length on off, Karunaratne works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Fullish ball on off, Dickwella pushes it to cover.
Very full ball on off, Dickwella gets his bat down in time and defends it to cover.
Full ball outside off, ND lets it go to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone by Dickwella.
Good length ball outside off, Dickwella shoulders arms to this one.
Very wide outside off, Karunaratne just watches it go through to the keeper.
FOUR! Nicely driven by Karunaratne. A fullish ball on middle, Karunaratne prods forward and leans on the drive as the ball races past the mid on fielder. He moves to 87 now.
Length ball outside off, left alone.

FOUR! EDGY! A length ball outside off, Karunaratne looks to cut but gets the outside edge just over du Plessis at second slip who tries his best to take it, but couldn't hold onto it. The ball races away to the third man fence. Karunaratne moves into the 90s. Sri Lanka now lead by 2Â runs.
Length ball outside off, Karunaratne lets it go through to the keeper.
Back of a length outside off, Karunaratne looks to cut but gets an inside edge which just misses the stumps. Living dangerously here is the Sri Lankan captain.
PLAY AND A MISS! Full ball outside off, Dickwella looks to drive but it sneaks under his bat and it goes to the keeper.
EDGY! Very lucky for Dickwella! Good length ball outside off, Dickwella looks to push at it but it takes the inside edge and goes past the off stump to de Kock.
Back of a length ball on off, Dickwella defends it to mid off.
Short ball on off, Dickwella plays it to deep point for a single.

Uppish but safe! Quinton de Kock is down on his haunches! HeÂ cannot believe it! Good length ball on middle, Karunaratne looks to flick but gets a top edge and it goes over the bowler and it lands safely.
On middle, Dimuth defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length around off, Dickwella pushes it towards point. Thinks for a run but decides against it.
EDGY! A fuller length ball just around off, Dickwella looks to defend but gets an outside edge which falls short of Markram at third slip and they take a brace before he returns the ball back.
Length ball around off, lets it go through to the keeper.
Fuller ball on the pads, Dickwella looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads as the ball lobs behind to the keeper.
A length ball outside off, Dickwella leaves that alone.
Fuller ball outside off, shapes away after pitching. Dickwella lets it go. With that it's Stumps on Day 2.
Nortje is on the money straightaway. A length ball around off, Dimuth pushes it towards point.
Shortish ball around off, Karunaratne hops and defends it towards square leg. The extra bounce on this delivery hurried up the Lankan skipper.
First runs for Sri Lanka and Karunaratne. A shortish ball around off, tucked away towards fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Nicely played. Shortish ball outside off, Dickwella punches it through the gap between third slip and gully and gets his first boundary of the morning.
Length ball around off, Dickwella leaves that alone.

Back of a length on middle, Dickwella stands tall and defends it back towards the bowler. Nortje picks and tries to throw the ball at the stumps at the striker's end. Some aggression first up from Nortje.
Starts with a shortish length ball outside off, Karunaratne shoulders arms and it travels to de Kock at a good height.
This time Ngidi angles in a fuller length ball on middle, Karunaratne flicks it through square leg for a run, moves to 93.
Pitches it full and keeps it close to off, Dickwella is half-forward as he defends it to the off side.
A length ball around off, shaping in, Dickwella defends it with an angled bat.
Good leave. That's a tempter by Ngidi. On a length and close to off. It holds its line as well. Niroshan shoulders arms.

FOUR! Shot! Ngidi thrives for movement and ends up bowling a juicy half-volley outside off. Dickwella plays a check-drive, finds good timing and placement to fetch a boundary at covers. The stand crosses fifty now, a very handy one!
FOUR! Excellent drive! A slightly overpitched ball around off, Karunaratne leans into the drive and plays it through the covers. On 97 now is Karunaratne.

FOUR! CENTURY! A captain's innings here from Dimuth Karunaratne. His 10th Test ton and he brings up in style. A shortish ball outside off, Karunaratne cuts that one through the cover-point region and gets to a well deserved hundred. It's been a struggle for him in South Africa and this knock will give him a lot of confidence.

Ohh that shoots up from a length. A shortish length ball around middle, Dimuth is hurried up as he hops and tucks this one towards square leg. His bottom hand came off the bat as he tried to play that ball.
BEATEN! Beautiful from Nortje. A length ball around off, jags back in and gets past Dickwella's inside edge through to de Kock.
Length ball around off, Dickwella blocks this out.
Back of a length around off, Dickwella pushes it with soft hands towards point and takes a quick run.
Ngidi speeds in from 'round the wicket and serves a good length ball outside off. It takes off after landing as Niroshan offers no shot. De Kock collects it over his head with a jump.

FOUR! Airborne but it's in the gap! Not quite a half-volley, it's outside off, Dickwella gets forward and drives it uppishly through cover-point. Good positive start for Sri Lanka, already 24 runs added to the overnight lead.
Play and a miss! Gets carried away, the Lankan wicketkeeper. Shortish and on off, Dickwella hangs back to whackÂ it over point but the bounce gets big on himÂ and it flies over his bat.
Plenty of movement on this ball. A length delivery close to off, it nips away after hitting the deck and Niroshan leaves it alone.
Good length delivery outside off, left alone by Niroshan.
The length is slightly fuller than usual, outside off, Dickwella presses forward and pushes it towards wide mid off.
Back of a length around middle, Karunaratne hops and tucks this one towards square leg.
Quick run. A length ball outside off, Dimuth looks to cut but the ball hits the outer part of the bat and goes towards point. Bavuma there has a shy at the non-striker's end but misses.
Plenty of bounce on this pitch. A shortish length around off, hurries Karunaratne as he hops and tucks thisÂ to the left of square leg for a run.
Length ball outside off, pushed towards covers.

OUT! CAUGHT! Nortje strikes. A back of a length ball into the body, Karunaratne tries to play the Nataraja pull shot but is hurried by the extra pace and gets a top edge that balloonsÂ towards square leg. Mulder takes one of the easiest catches there but after taking it blinks his eyes as if to tell, he nearly lost it in the sky. A fine innings by Karunaratne is over. South Africa are elated as they get the prized wicket of the Sri Lankan skipper. The lead is 31.
A bouncer on middle, Dickwella ducks and de Kock fails to collect. It goes behind and there is a long stop. They cross for a bye.
On a good length and wide outside off, an easy leave for Dickwella.

FOUR! Nicely played by Dickwella. A back of a length delivery outside off, at 132 kph, Dickwella allows the ball to come to him and then just uses the bounce to steer it behind backward point. There was a man at the fence but it was played wide of him.

OUT! One brings two and all of a sudden, Sri Lanka have lost both their overnight batsmen. Ngidi hurls across a fuller length ball around off, there is a slight away deviation as it hits the deck and Dickwella decides to heave it over the leg side. The ball nips away to take the leading half of his bat and flies in the air at covers. Bavuma sprints across to his right and takes the skier easily. Four wickets for Lungi and he has been South Africa's best bowler in the second innings. Sri Lanka are effectively 36/6!
A length ball on off, Hasaranga drives it off his front foot to covers.
A slight bit of inward movement from outside off, Wanindu defends it close to his front pad.
Targets the off stump with a fuller length ball, Hasaranga does well to block it from the crease. End of another successful over for the Proteas.
Fuller length ball in the channel outside off, Shanaka is not interested in playing that.
A length ball, but still wide outside off, for Shanaka to play at it. Left alone.
Length outside off, Shanaka shoulders arms to it.
Nortje goes wide of the crease, bowls a length ball outside off, Shanaka is smart to leave that one.
A bumper now around off, Shanaka sways away from it.
Almost gets his man. A length ball around off, shapes away after pitching. Shanaka looks to defend but the ball misses the outside edge by not much. Good over this by Nortje.
Good length ball on off, Hasaranga defends it back from the crease.
Uses the angle of the bowler and pushes a fuller length ball to mid on.
Beaten all ends up! Beautiful bowling. Ngidi angles in a fuller length ball around off, Hasaranga tries to defend but it shapes away off the seam to beat the outside edge. Unplayable.

Beaten comprehensively once again! Action replay of the last delivery. Moving away from the batsman off the seam, this time Wanindu tries to force the issue by opting for a big shot down the ground. Misses and the ball wasn't too far away from the outside edge.
A length ball around off, Hasaranga pushes it with an angled bat to covers.
Watchful! Fuller and close to off, this one is nipping back in, Hasaranga lands his front foot towards and defends it back. End of a probing over by Lungi.
Shortish around off, Shanaka rocks back and tucks this one towards square leg to get off the mark.
Hasaranga too is off the mark as he pushes a length ball around off towards cover-point for a single.
Length ball outside off, Shanaka comes forward and shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length coming in with the angle, Shanaka tucks this one towards deep square leg for a run.
Ohh, That bounced from a length. A length ball outside off, shapes away after pitching. Hasaranga looks to cut but the ball bounces above the bat. A wry smile on Hasaranga's face.
Back of a length on middle, defended back towards the bowler.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
FOUR! Superb shot! Lovely wristwork shown by Shanaka. Too full and straight from Ngidi, Dasun rotates his wrists and flicks it supremely through mid-wicket for a boundary. The lead is now 43.
Good length delivery outside off, Shanaka plants his front foot forward and then makes a leave.
Angling into the batsman from outside off, on a length, Shanaka gets forward and pushes it with gentle hands to cover-point for a brisk run.
On middle, angling in, Hasaranga gets back and defends it by closing the face of his bat. It rolls to short mid-wicket.
Probes with a fuller length ball on off, Wanindu stays back and offers a dead bat in defense. The search for a fifer continues for Ngidi!
Fuller length just outside off, Shanaka lets it go through to de Kock.
Slightly shortish outside off, Shanaka watches it closely and then sways away from it. He keeps his bat away from the ball.
Length ball outside off, Shanaka is confident in his leave.
Length ball but too wide outside off, Shanaka watches it go to the keeper.
Probing Shanaka outside off with a length ball, but Shanaka is not interested in playing that.
Back of a length on middle, Shanaka tucks this one towards fine leg for a single. Good batting this by Shanaka making Nortje bowl at the stumps.
Good length ball on off, defended off the back foot by Shanaka.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Shortish and outside off, Dasun pushes it towards cover-point and eyes a run but is sent back.
Fuller length ball on off, angling in, Shanaka solidly blocks it to the off side.

OUT! Mulder fools the batsman with a slower one. He dishes out a fuller length ball on middle at 123 kph, Shanaka is early into his shot as he attempts to whip it across the line. Ends up ballooning a simple catch to Sipamla at mid on. Another soft dismissal this morning for the visiting team.Â Sri Lanka are effectively 45/7!
Angles in a full length ball on off, staying a bit low, Chameera defends it from the back foot to the off side.
FOUR BYES! A short ball down the leg side, Hasaranga ducks under it. The ball bounces over de Kock and runs to the boundary. Bonus runs for Sri Lanka, their lead is one short of touching 50.
Length ball on middle and leg, Hasaranag plays it back to the bowler.
Bumper aroundÂ  middle and leg, Shanaka ducks under it and lets it go.
Back of a length around middle, tucked towards square leg.
Short of a length on middle, Hasaranga tucks this towards deep square leg and takes a run. The initial call was for twoÂ but the fielder in the deepÂ does well to keep it to a single.
Another bumper on middle, Chameera ducks under it.

Dropped? Seems that it fell just short of Maharaj. Fuller length ball on middle and leg, Hasaranga flicks it across the line and it drops short of Keshav at mid-wicket. He does well to dive and stop it from racing away.
Back of a length ball outside off, Hasaranga hangs back and steers it through point for a brace.
FOUR! A leg stump half-volley and Hasaranga cashes in. He leans forward and across before flicking it wide of Maharaj at mid-wicket for a boundary. 200 up for Sri Lanka.
Gets on the front foot to a length ball and pushes it to covers.

On a length and outside off, staying a touch low, Wanindu does well to ease it through point. They collect a couple as Ngidi was a bit lazy in attacking the ball. He eventually fires in a wild throw at the striker's end. Maharaj jumps to back up the throw but it brushes his fingers and goes behind. An overthrow is conceded. De Kock is seen shaking his head. Dushmantha has only one ball to survive.
Just one ball to negotiate and Chameera does well by leaving a length ball outside off.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Short ball on middle and leg, Hasaranga ducks under it.
Length ball on leg stump, Hasaranga shuffles and clips this one towards fine leg for a run.
The plan is to bowl short here. A bumper on middle and leg, Chameera sits under it.
A length ball around off, Chameera pushes this one towards point.
Ends the over with a fuller length ball around off. Chameera looks to drive but the ball sneaks through to the keeper.
Around off, that is defended solidly off the front foot.
Full length ball angling in from around off, Hasaranga defends it quite comfortably.
FOUR! Streaky one! Fuller in length and outside off, Hasaranga attempts a loose drive at it and gets a thick outside edge wide of gully for a boundary.
Oooohhhh... that missed the outside edge and the off stump by a whisker. This one pitches on a length close to off and straightens, Wanindu is squared up in defense and gets beaten all ends up.

OUT! Sound of timber! A peach of a delivery followed by a slightly fuller length ball around off, shaping in. Hasaranga possibly got rattled by the last delivery, tries to chance his arm and look for a big shot. Misses the ball completely and has his stumps destroyed. Sipamla is absolutely pumped, he had to wait for his chance and has managed to leave his impact straightaway. Sri Lanka lose their fourth wicket this morning and are effectively 64/8!
Too full in length on middle, it's worked through square leg and they cross for a run.
Length ball around off, Fernando defends this one tentatively.
Length ball around off, jags back in and thuds into the pads of Fernando, who misses the flick shot.

NOT OUT! A peach of a ball from Ngidi. Length ball around off, shapes just a little away and goes through the defense of Fernando. There was a noise and the umpire had his finger up. Review taken straightaway. Replays show that the ball hit the back pocket and not his bat. However Ultra Edge detects nothing as the ball passes the bat. The umpire overturns his decision. Ngidi has to wait for his 5-fer here.
A length ball on off, keeping low, Fernando defends it to the off side.
Sliding down the leg side, Vishwa tries flicking but misses.
Good length delivery outside off, Fernando has tame push inside the line as he misses.
Beaten! Sipamla is in a really good rhythm. Serves a back of a length ball on off, nipping away, Chameera pushes and misses.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Good length ball on off, Chameera tries to defend it from the back foot but gets it away of the outside edge to point. Looks for a run but is sent back.

OUT! Number 9 goes down! Superb delivery. A touch short and juts outside off, Chameera feels for it inside the line with zero footwork and gets a faint outside edge behind. Quinton de Kock catches it and appeals but nothing from the umpire. The DRS is taken quickly and Ultra Edge finds a spike.
Play and a miss! Fullish length wide outside off, Asitha throws his bat at it but fails to connect.

OUT! Off stump goes for a walk! Sipamla steams in and darts in a pacy length ball around off, it skids on after landing, beating the defensive bat of Asitha. It goes on to uproot the off stump and Sri Lanka are all out for 211!
FOUR! SHOT!Â  Not a good way to start when you are defending peanuts. A short and wide ball outside off, Markram rocks back and forcesÂ this one through cover-point for his first boundary.
A length ball around middle, bounces a tad extra and hits Markram high on his bat. He tucks this one towards mid-wicket and takes a run.
Length ball outside off, Elgar allows it go through to the keeper.
Beaten! A length ball around off, shapes away after pitching. Elgar looks to defend but the ball beats the outside edge on its way to the keeper.
Length ball around off, DeanÂ pushes it towards covers.
First runs for Elgar. A length ball around off, Elgar pushes it in the gap at covers and comes back for a brace before the fielder returns the ball.
Starts with a gentle good length ball outside off, Aiden shoulders arms.

Lands it on a length close to off, shaping away, Markram pushes it with an angled bat to point. Initially, he looks for a run but then he realizes that he has hit it too well. There is a fielder in the vicinity and immediately, Markram shouts a loud no.
On a length and around off, it's blocked well of the back foot.
Fuller in length and on off, Markram drives it back to the bowler.
Too full and on off, Markram drives again but this time towards mid off.
Movement back into the batsman with extra bounce, Markram keeps it out with one hand.
FOUR! Nicely done. A length ball around off, shaping away. Elgar plays that with soft hands towards the gap between slips and gully and collects a boundary. Nice bit of wristwork by the southpaw.
Length ball around off, Elgar pushes it towards point and calls his partner for a quick single.
Back of a length ball around off, Markram hops and keeps this one out.
Nicely punched off the back foot. A back of a length ball around off, Markram rocks back and punches this one through the covers and collects a brace.
Length ball around middle, Markram tucks this one towards deep square and takes a single.
Length ball around off, Elgar defends this one with soft hands towards gully.
Full and floated on middle, knocked wide of mid on for a run.
Too full in length on middle, Elgar flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Misfield and FOUR! Very full in length outside off, Markram drills his drive to the left of mid off. Shanaka moves there, slides but it goes through his legs for a boundary.
Tossed up ball on off, a googly, defended by Markram.
Loopy and full on off, Markram presses forward in defense.
Works a full ball to the right of mid-wicket and collects a single.Â  45 needed more!
Length ball around middle, Markram stands tall and defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length around off, Markram pushes this one towards point.
No run.

NOT OUT! A close one this. A fuller length ball outside off, Markram looks to drive but gets an outside edge towards the slip cordon. Mendis from second slip dives across to his left and claims the catch. Markram stands his ground and the umpires send it upstairs by giving the soft signal as out. Replays show the ball has touched the ground as Mendis caught it. There is enough conclusive evidence to overturn the soft signal and the third umpire flashes NOT OUT on the big screen. Markram survives.
A length ball on middle and leg, nudged through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Back of a length ball on off, Aiden Markram punches it off his back foot to cover-point. That will be LUNCH ON DAY 3!
FOUR! What a dessert to get after Lunch. A short and wide ball outside off, Elgar punches this one off the back foot through the covers.
Shortish on middle, Elgar pulls this one towards deep square leg for a single.
Length ball around off,Â  Markram pushes thisÂ towards point and takes a quick single.
FOUR! SHOT! A wide ball outside off, Elgar throws his hands at that one and plays through the gully region to collectÂ his second boundary of the over. South Africa look in a hurry here.
Length ball around off, Elgar pushes this one towards extra cover.
Nice bumper to finish the over. A short ball around middle and leg, Elgar ducks and then tries to pull but it misses his bat through to the keeper.

Pops up in the air... DROPS SAFELY! Vishwa runs in from 'round the wicket and digs in a short ball on middle. Markram jumps to fend it off and it takes the shoulder of his bat. It lobs in the air but dies down near the surface. No short leg there otherwise he would have been in business.
Shortish and on off, it's punched off the back foot to point where the fielder fumbles slightly but no run taken.
Stays on the back foot and uses the angle of the bowler to work it in the gap at mid-wicket. A couple is taken.
A length delivery just outside off, staying a bit low, Markram defends it well from the crease.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and pushes it to mid off.
FOUR! Boom! Width on offer outside off, fuller in length, Markram attacks it with all his might and bludgeons his drive through covers. 27 needed more!
Shortish around middle, Elgar rocks back and pulls it away towards deep square for a single.
Good length ball on middle, Markram watches it closely and blocks it out.
Length ball, a bit of away shape, outside off, Markram pushes it towards covers.
Fuller length outside off, Markram shoulders arms to it.
Beaten! That one kept low. A length ball around off, shapes away a little, beating the outside edge of Markram's bat as he tries to push.
Length ball around off, Markram is compact in his front foot defense.
A length delivery outside off, punched from the back foot to covers.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Stays on the back foot to a good length ball and pushes it to covers again.
Pitches it up and around off, Elgar mistimes his drive off the inner half to mid on.
FOUR! Nicely placed! Back of a length ball around off, shaping back in, Elgar hangs back inside the crease and steers it through the gap between gully and point.
Whoa! This is a shot Elgar never plays. Attempts to muscle his drive through the cover region butÂ he misses the ball badly. With no pressure, Dean is trying something out of his comfort zone.
Length ball in the channel outside off, shapes away, Markram lets it go.
Length ball outside off, Markram watches it go through to the keeper.
MISFIELD AND FOUR! A fullish ball outside off, Markram prods forward and drives this one past the fielder at covers, who fails to stop that and the ball races away to the fence.

Good length ball outside off, Markram plays it towards gully. The fielder gets a hand to it and takes the pace off the ball. It rolls behindÂ and a couple is taken. 50 partnership with that couple between Markram and Elgar!
Another two. This time a length ball around off, Markram playsÂ it through the cover-point area and comes back for the second.
Length ball around off, punched towards point for another run.
Good length delivery outside off, shaping away, Markram stays back and punches it to sweeper cover for a run.
Tries to tempt Elgar by bowling a full ball wide outside off, the southpaw is not going after it.
Excellent delivery! Angling into the batsman on a length and nipping away, Elgar pushes at itÂ and misses.
Short in length and outside off, Elgar forces it off the back foot to deep cover for one.
Angles in a length ball on middle and leg, Markram works it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs. Under 10 needed now.
Hurls across a good length delivery outside off, shaping away, Aiden shoulders arms.
Floated around leg, Elgar tucks this one towards deep square leg for a run.
Shortish around off, Markram worksÂ this one towards mid-wicket.
Floated ball around off, Markram defends it towardsÂ cover.
Floated around off, Markram plays that one towards cover for no run.
Flatter and on middle, helped in the gap at mid-wicket for a run.
FOUR! Put away! Short and wide outside off, Elgar doesn't need a second invitation to attack it. He rocks back, makes room and whacks it through covers.
Good length delivery outside off, pushed off the back foot to covers.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Outside off, left alone.
On and around off, defended from the crease to covers.
Gets behind the line of the fuller length ball and pushes it back to the bowler.
A back foot defense to complete a maiden over. 3 needed more.
Floated around middle and leg, Elgar pushes this one softly towards long on and takes a couple of runs. Scores level with that two runs.

That's the winning run! Floated around middle and leg, Elgar tucks this one towards deep mid-wicketÂ and takes a single to celebrateÂ with his hands up. South Africa win by 10 wickets and take the series 2-0!
